Full Title: Annual Research Forum of the LSHK 
Short Title: LSHK-ARF 2008 

Date: 06-Dec-2008 - 07-Dec-2008
Location: Hong Kong, Hong Kong 
Contact Person: Sze-Wing Tang
Meeting Email: lshk.arf2008@gmail.com
Web Site: http://www.lshk.org 

Linguistic Field(s): General Linguistics 

Call Deadline: 20-Oct-2008 

Meeting Description:

The 2008 Annual Research Forum of the Linguistic Society of Hong Kong will be
hosted by the University of Hong Kong, on December 6-7, 2008. The theme of this
year's ARF is 'From Theory to Practice'. Our keynote speaker is Professor
Suzanne Flynn from MIT. As is customary ARF practice, there will be multiple
parallel sessions and papers related to any areas of linguistics are strongly
encouraged. 

Call for Papers

Each paper will be allotted 20 minutes for oral presentation and 10 minutes for
discussion. 

Please note that all presenters (or at least one of them in a co-authored paper)
have to be an LSHK member. Each member is maximally entitled to one
single-author presentation and one joint presentation. Each submission will be
an abstract of no more than 400 words in English or 800 characters in Chinese.
Abstract submissions and registration will be done online at www.lshk.org. Email
and/or paper abstract submissions will NOT be accepted. 

Authors of selected presentations will be invited to submit a paper for
inclusion in the Selected Papers to be published by the Society.



	
